label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp72

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the brain, near to the antler (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has postsynapses and presynapses in the ipsilateral inferior posterior slope and also has presynapses in the gnathal ganglion (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the VNC, it follows the intermediate tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus - commissure of fine fibers (Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 1-2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

definition.value: Type identified at light level and matched across EM datasets by Sturner et al. (2024). Pre- or post-synapse locations are the fewest regions that collectively contain at least 80 percent of all pre- or post-synapses of these neurons in FlyWire.

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp73

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the brain, posterior-lateral to the inferior bridge (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has postsynapses in the saddle, the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center and the gnathal ganglion (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has presynapses in the contralateral inferior posterior slope, the gnathal ganglion and the saddle (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the VNC, it follows the median tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus I (Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

definition.value: Type identified at light level and matched across EM datasets by Sturner et al. (2024). Pre- or post-synapse locations are the fewest regions that collectively contain at least 80 percent of all pre- or post-synapses of these neurons in FlyWire.

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp38

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the brain, posterior to the inferior bridge (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It belongs to the PSp2 lineage (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has postsynapses and presynapses in the ipsilateral anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, the saddle, the ipsilateral wedge and the gnathal ganglion (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

definition.value: Type identified at light level and matched across EM datasets by Sturner et al. (2024). Pre- or post-synapse locations are the fewest regions that collectively contain at least 80 percent of all pre- or post-synapses of these neurons in FlyWire. Different MANC individuals are assigned different VNC tracts (Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp49

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the brain, posterior-ventral to the mushroom body calyx (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It belongs to the PSp3 lineage (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has postsynapses in the ipsilateral and contralateral superior posterior slope, and the ipsilateral inferior clamp and inferior bridge, and presynapses in the gnathal ganglion (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the VNC, it follows the dorsal lateral tract of ventral cervical fasciculus (Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp58

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the brain, ventral to the mushroom body calyx (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It belongs to the SMPpv2 lineage (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has postsynapses and presynapses in the prow and the ipsilateral flange, and also has presynapses in the contralateral flange (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the VNC, it follows the curved ventrolateral tract (Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is serotonin (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp65

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the brain, posterior to the antler (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It is a putative embryonic-born neuron (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has postsynapses and presynapses in the prow and the ipsilateral flange, and also has presynapses in the contralateral flange (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the VNC, it follows the median dorsal abdominal tract (Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is GABA (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron outside of the brain DNx02

value.value: Adult sensory neuron with its soma in the periphery (Schlegel et al., 2024). It enters the brain via the occipital nerve and in the brain, it remains restricted to the gnathal ganglion (Sturner et al., 2024). In the ventral nerve cord (VNC) it projects to the neck and haltere neuropils on both sides (Sturner et al., 2024). It has substantial output to AN06B025 in both the brain and VNC (Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are two of these cells on each side (Schlegel et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2023).

Adult visual projection neuron with its soma in the brain, ventral-medial to the accessory medulla (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has postsynapses in the ipsilateral lobula (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has presynapses in the ipsilateral superior clamp, the ipsilateral posterior lateral protocerebrum and the ipsilateral lobula (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 3 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

Neurotransmitter predictions are from Eckstein et al. (2024). Other annotations are based on annotations in FlyWire and are available in the supplemental material of Schlegel et al. (2024).
